Purpose and Scope

This document will outline integration between the Industrial Financial System (IFS) application suite and the Cost Estimate System (CES).

Currently, IFS Interface application processes the data in three steps:

1.	Extract Cost Estimation Data from the IFS Oracle database through views, defined as follows:
a.	TTC_INTERFACE_CES_PartMaster
b.	TTC_INTERFACE_CES_text_data
c.	TTC_INTERFACE_CES_PartDesc
d.	TTC_INTERFACE_CES_PartOrder

2.	Perform necessary transformations (If required)

3.	Write data to the CES database

CES rewrite includes migration of CES database from Oracle to MS SQL server.

Table Mappings:

•	TTC_INTERFACE_CES_PartDesc maps to CES.SBCES.VendorPartDesc
•	TTC_INTERFACE_CES_ PartOrder maps to CES.SBCES.PartOrder
•	TTC_INTERFACE_CES_PartMaster maps to CES.SBCES.PartMaster
•	TTC_INTERFACE_CES_ text_data maps to CES.SBCES.TextData

